Creating the simulation¶

In [6]:
def fu_laser(kz, r):
    """
    Top-hat spot with the Gaussian temporal profile
    """ 
    profile_r = np.exp( -( r/R_las )**40 )
    profile_r *= ( r < 0.99 * Rmax ) + (r>= 0.99 * Rmax)
    profile_kz = np.exp( -( (kz-k0) * c * tau / 2 )**2 )
    return profile_r * profile_kz
In [7]:
def mirror_axiparabola_num(kz, r, f0, d0, R, N_cut=4):
    """
    Spectra-radial phase representing on-axis Axiparabola
    [Smartsev et al Opt. Lett. 44, 3414 (2019)]
    """
    s_ax = np.zeros_like(r)
    r_loc = r[N_cut:]

    sag_equation = lambda r, s : (s - (f0 + d0 * r**2 / R**2) + \
                        np.sqrt(r**2 + ((f0 + d0 * r**2 / R**2)-s)**2)) / r

    s_ax[N_cut:] = solve_ivp(sag_equation, (r_loc[0], r_loc[-1]), 
        [r_loc[0]/(4*f0),], t_eval=r_loc, method='DOP853', 
        rtol=1e-13, atol=1e-16).y.flatten()

    s_ax[:N_cut] = s_ax[N_cut]
    s_ax -= s_ax[0]

    kz2d = ( kz * np.ones((*kz.shape, *r.shape)).T ).T
    phi = -2 * s_ax[None,:] * kz2d

    print(f'Full sag {s_ax.ptp()/lambda0:g} wavelengths')
    return np.exp(1j * phi)
